The police have arrested three men for allegedly gang-r*ping a 14-year-old girl in Lagos.The suspects, David Gideon, 21, Sodiq Olayitan, 24, and Mubarak Tajudeen, 23, were said to have abducted, gagged and took turns to r*pe the victim at Lakeview Estate, Phase Two, Amuwo Odofin. It was learnt that the incident occurred around 5:30pm on February 14 and the boys who committed the crime were four.Police spokesman Adekunle Ajisebutu said efforts were on to arrest the fourth suspect.Ajisebutu said the police moved to the scene as soon as they received information, adding that they recovered a cutlass, dagger, hammer and charms from the suspects.He said the suspects have been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCID), Panti at the instance of the Commissioner of Police (CP) Abiodun Alabi, for discreet investigation, adding that the victim was rushed to the hospital for treatment.  source By Zubairu Idris Katsina - The police in Katsina State have arrested three teenage boys in Danmusa Local Government Area for allegedly gang raping and drowning a 13-year-old girl to death in a pond. Police Spokesman in the state, SP Gambo Isah, disclosed this during a press briefing on Wednesday… In "News" By Oladapo Udom Lagos - The Lagos State Commissioner of Police ( CP) Zubairu Muazu  on Monday said that the State Police Command arrested 40 armed robbery suspects, 29 suspected cultists, and 19 suspects for murder in the last one month. (L-R) Lagos State PPRO, DSP Bala Elkana listening as … In "Metro" Lagos - The Rapid Response Squad (RRS) under the Lagos State Police Command said on Sunday that it arrested three teenage robbery suspects on Friday in the Ajegunle area of the state. This is contained in a statement by the Police/Public Relations Officer of the Command, SP Oladapo Badmus. According… In "Metro"